; =============================================================
; PROTEIN DATABASE — COMPLETE, ALL REAL SEQUENCES
; =============================================================
; Species: Klebsiella pneumoniae, Escherichia coli, Acinetobacter
; baumannii (NDM-1's real clinical host range).
;
; The evolutionary link between the target enzyme and the structural
; homolog runs through METALLO-beta-lactamases (zinc-dependent, class
; B — e.g. NDM), NOT serine beta-lactamases (class A — TEM, SHV) or
; class D (OXA). Both metallo-beta-lactamases and tRNase Z belong to
; the same ancient "MBL-fold" superfamily (Daiyasu et al. 2001; Lee,
; Takahashi, Jeon et al. 2019, on PNGM-1 — the enzyme with measured
; dual metallo-beta-lactamase AND tRNase Z activity that pins down
; this evolutionary relationship. See presentation/PROJECT_EXPLAINER.md
; Section 2b for the full story, it's genuinely worth knowing well.)
;
; NOTE on the Acinetobacter lactamase entry: it's from Acinetobacter
; sp. NF512, a close relative of A. baumannii, kept deliberately —
; NDM-1 spreads via horizontal plasmid transfer (Tn125 transposon)
; rather than vertical inheritance, so this sequence being virtually
; identical to the K. pneumoniae entry despite the species difference
; is itself the evidence for Finding 1 in the Discussion section.
;
; Header convention: >CLASS|SPECIES|GENE|ACCESSION description
;   CLASS is one of: LACTAMASE, TRNASE_Z, TF
; =============================================================

