; =============================================================
; FOURTH CLASS — SERINE_LACTAMASE (added for convergent evolution comparison)
; =============================================================
; Serine beta-lactamases do the SAME JOB as the metallo-beta-lactamase
; above (destroy penicillin-family antibiotics) but are NOT related to
; it by ancestry — they evolved independently from penicillin-binding
; proteins (PBPs), a completely different lineage than the MBL-fold
; superfamily. This is convergent evolution: two unrelated solutions
; to the same problem. It's the mirror case of the LACTAMASE/TRNASE_Z
; pair above (which is divergent evolution: related ancestry, different
; function). Expect alignment scores between SERINE_LACTAMASE and
; LACTAMASE to be LOW despite both being "beta-lactamases" by name —
; if this comparison scored HIGH, that would actually be the surprising
; result worth investigating further.

